headline: Investing Heavily in AI as Models Improve: GoDaddy CEO
summary: Aman Bhutani, GoDaddy CEO, says the company's AI transformation is focused on generative AI tools. He tells Katie Greifeld and David Gura on "The Close" that by the end of this year, GoDaddy aims for 70% of its code to be AI-generated.

headline: GDDY Q3 Deep Dive: AI Strategy and Product Expansion Drive Customer Engagement
summary: Domain registrar and web services company GoDaddy (NYSE:GDDY) reported Q3 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 10.3% year on year to $1.27 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $1.27 billion was less impressive, coming in 0.5% below analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $1.51 per share was 3.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
